            "minVersion": "15.0",
            "projectUrl": "https://helpx.adobe.com/content/dam/help/en/premiere-pro/how-to/in-app/031-reframe-your-project-multiple-platforms/Reframe_for_multiple_platforms-project.prproj",
            "sizeBytes": "123456789",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "text": "Reframe your project for different social platforms",
                            "type": "heading"
                        },
                        {
                            "autoplay": true,
                            "loop": true,
                            "type": "video",
                            "videoUrl": "https://helpx.adobe.com/content/dam/help/en/premiere-pro/how-to/in-app/031-reframe-your-project-multiple-platforms/e96d88e2-766a-4356-8308-8c2fc6a22193.mp4"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "<br>You'll often upload your content to multiple social media platforms with different aspect ratio requirements. The video you've worked on in the previous tutorials is currently 16:9 and would look great on YouTube. But if you also want to upload it to Instagram, you'd need to change the aspect ratio to 1:1.",
                            "type": "text"
                        },
                        {
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "projectItemsSelected",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "countMin": 1
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "text": "In the <$Project$> panel, select the \"Self Care\" sequence."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "In the main menu, choose <$Sequence$> > <$Auto Reframe Sequence$> (the option is near the bottom)."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "In the <$Auto Reframe Sequence$> window, under <$Target Aspect Ratio$> choose <$Square 1:1$>."
                                },
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "projectItemAdded",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "itemType": "sequence"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Perfect!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "Premiere Pro created a new sequence with a 1:1 aspect ratio in the Project panel, in a new folder named \"Auto Reframed Sequences.\" You can return to the original sequence and create as many automatically reframed sequences as you like in different aspect ratios. Play through the new sequence and see how it looks. If you're not happy with the results, in the next step you'll learn how to tweak the Auto Reframe effect manually."
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "text": "Leave the other settings unchanged, then click <$Create$>."
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "listSubsteps"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "autoplay": true,
                            "loop": true,
                            "type": "video",
                            "videoUrl": "https://helpx.adobe.com/content/dam/help/en/premiere-pro/how-to/in-app/031-reframe-your-project-multiple-platforms/cbb1b50c-0b86-42cb-8041-b5d95a5538fd.mp4"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Fine-tune the Auto Reframe effect",
                            "type": "heading"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "Results with Auto Reframe will differ depending on your footage, but generally it works extremely well. In this case, the Auto Reframe did a fantastic job! However, there are a few places we can fine-tune the Auto Reframe effect by manually adjusting keyframes.",
                            "type": "text"
                        },
                        {
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiMoved"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "text": "Watch the Auto Reframed sequence and look for any places that need adjustment."
                                },
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "isPanelOpen",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "panelName": "Effect Controls"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Perfect!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "The <$Effect Controls$> panel is where you will manually adjust the Auto Reframe effect. In the next step, you'll reveal the keyframes that Auto Reframe has generated in the Timeline view of the <$Effect Controls$> panel, and change those keyframes to adjust the effect."
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "text": "In the main menu, choose <$Window$> > <$Effect Controls$>."
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "listSubsteps"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "text": "Adjust keyframes",
                            "type": "heading"
                        },
                        {
                            "autoplay": true,
                            "loop": true,
                            "type": "video",
                            "videoUrl": "https://helpx.adobe.com/content/dam/help/en/premiere-pro/how-to/in-app/031-reframe-your-project-multiple-platforms/0a163c7a-dfb0-42ae-bda1-c7b974a735e8.mp4"
                        },
                        {
                            "text": "<br>Near the end of the clip \"Meeting02.mp4,\" Auto Reframe did not keep the man near the center of the frame. You can adjust or delete keyframes to make sure he stays centered in frame.",
                            "type": "text"
                        },
                        {
                            "listItems": [
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiMoved"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "isCtiOverClip",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "clipName": "Meeting02.mp4"
                                            }
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "isClipSelected",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "clipName": "Meeting02.mp4"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "text": "Move the playhead to the beginning of the clip \"Meeting02.mp4\" and make sure that it is selected."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Look for the <$Auto Reframe$> effect in the <$Effect Controls$> panel and check the Under the <$Adjust Position$> property, check the <$Overwrite generated path$> box to reveal the position keyframes."
                                },
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiMoved"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiStopped"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "isCtiOverClip",
                                            "payload": {
                                                "clipName": "Meeting02.mp4"
                                            }
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "text": "In the Timeline view of the <$Effect Controls$> panel, move the playhead to the first keyframe of the \"Meeting02.mp4\" clip."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Drag the X value (the first blue number) until the man is centered in the frame. Delete the remaining three keyframes."
                                },
                                {
                                    "text": "Move the playhead to the end of the clip and change the X value to about 450 so that he remains closer to the center of the frame."
                                },
                                {
                                    "checkUserInteractions": [
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiMoved"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiStopped"
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "check": "ctiMoved"
                                        }
                                    ],
                                    "showOnComplete": {
                                        "heading": "Perfect!",
                                        "texts": [
                                            "When you play back the clip, the man should now stay in the center of the shot because you adjusted the keyframes."
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    "text": "Press <%â†‘%> and then <%{KEY.SPACEBAR}%> to play back the newly reframed clip."
                                }
                            ],
                            "type": "listSubsteps"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "stepItems": [
                        {
                            "successHeading": "Nicely done!",
                            "successText": "You just changed the aspect ratio of the sequence. Your video is now ready to export and upload to multiple social platforms. For a deeper dive into these topics and more, visit the <a href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/premiere-pro/tutorials.html\">Adobe help pages</a>.",
                            "type": "endScreen"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
